rComments: rude prof

Awful, boring class. The professor is insufferable, probably the worst prof I've had through my entire undergrad experience so far. The course content has potential to be cool and interesting if it was taught by someone who's actually enthusiastic about their job.

This class is very easy and a good way to boost GPA, but I'm not sure if even that is worth it. Extremely boring and disorganized lectures. Professor reads straight off the slides so the upside is that you don't have to attend her boring lectures. She is also unresponsive to emails and very rude. Would never take a class of hers again

Most boring thing I've ever experienced. Dr. Laposa's monotone and dry teaching method will make you stop going to lecture after the very first class. She's also unfriendly, unhelpful, and unapproachable. If you're taking this class be prepared to teach yourself everything from the posted slide as attending class will do nothing but bore u to death
rude professor

cant begin to describe how all over the place these lectures are. They're teaching science and science history in the most bizarre fashion. Lectures are more of "story time" and reading in the 3rd person off of slides as opposed to elaborating off of hard to understand topics.

Course material was kind of dry, she read off of the slides & so attending class wasn't necessary. She was always open to discussion and to answer questions, really approachable. I personally found her way of lecturing to be very uninspiring and difficult to stay engaged with. I'd take another one of her courses if I had to.
Terrible professor who wont pay exam investigator
A terrible professor who is arrogant, condescending, and extremely rude
made the project course unbearable
When she took over the course she changed it for the worse
Lectures were content heavy and everywhere, various content reused in later lectures. She reads off the slides so attendance isn't 100% necessary.
She's great! You just need to put in the work and you will be rewarded. She provides rubrics and is quite lenient with her marking.
No quality whatsoever

She was amazing, I love dr Rebecca Laposa. I take her art of drug discovery class, and she has helped me find one of my new greatest passions. The midterm was fair, and the class was fun. I hope I have her again, highly reccomend. Also she is quite beautiful :)) and her voice is great, very calming, especially when describing complex concepts
Terrible
BORING. If you do not have a self-interest in pharmacology you will fall asleep.
bad
Awful, boring, and rude. Extremely awkward as well.
Never replies to emails and extremely dismissive. Always seems like she doesn't want to talk to you. Mumbles during lecture and extremely boring.

She is a good professor. Midterms were fair and classes were pretty interesting. However, the essay paper was not fairly marked and also the exam was hard since it was cumulative covering 30+ lectures and all the associated readings, way too much.  She lost my liking in the end. Also, she needs to speak up in class, people can barely hear her.

She talks really softly during class and it's really hard to understand at times. She also speaks in a way that makes people fall asleep. In addition, she does not explain concepts thoroughly leaving many questions and doubts. In terms of midterms, questions can be tricky at times, so make sure you listen to recordings and make detailed notes.

Great course! The prof has pretty clear slides that are mostly self-explanatory. Lots of readings that may seem tedious, but they're very interesting to read and definitely help understand the concepts in lecture better. Prof wasn't the most exciting but she knows her stuff very well and answers questions very patiently and clearly.

The best class I took in first year, and I ended up applying to pharmacology because of her. Sometimes her lectures can feel drawn out by the end of the hour, but she always explains things very clearly (especially for students who are not in life sci). Tests are fair if you have studied your slides!! Paper is easy if you put some thought into it!
